# Dev Tooling MCP

**Trigger:** Datei/Klasse/Methode verstehen, `find_file`, `find_by_content`, `read_signatures_only`, `read_method`, `read_class_summary`, `ng generate`, `dotnet new`, Verzeichnisstruktur anlegen.

Skill: [dev-tooling-mcp/SKILL.md](../skills/dev-tooling-mcp/SKILL.md)

## Routing

| Situation | Aktion |
|-----------|--------|
| Nur Signaturen / eine Methode / Klassen-Überblick | dev-filesystem-mcp (`read_*`, `find_*`) |
| Angular scaffold | dev-angular-mcp |
| .NET-Projekt / Ordner | dev-dotnet-mcp |
| Review, Index, Komplexität, Refactoring-Safety | **codebase-analyzer** — nicht dev-filesystem |

## Kurzreferenz — dev-filesystem-mcp

- Pfade: `/project/...` (Docker ro-mount)
- `find_file(root, pattern)` — max 100
- `read_signatures_only(file_path)` — vor vollem `Read`
- `read_method(file_path, method_name)` — gezielter Body
- `read_class_summary(file_path)` — Struktur ohne Bodies
- `find_implementations(root, interface_name, language: auto)`

## Kurzreferenz — Scaffolding

- `scaffold_angular_component(project_root, name)` / `scaffold_angular_service(...)`
- `scaffold_dotnet_project(template, name, output_path)` / `create_directory_structure(base_path, paths_json)`
